In this new version of the app, we have several new features. Among other things, we have updated the look and feel of Savings and investment. You will find it by clicking on Savings and investment under the main menu. You can also manage your child's banking services, such as activating the app for young people. You can find this by going to Settings and then Managing Services. In addition, you can also apply for private loans together with another applicant. You do this by the main menu, click on Loans and then Calculate and apply for loans.

This version contains new functionality like:

- We have updated layout for all your accounts available in Savings and Investments (ISK, equity trader, fund account and endowment insurance). From now on you can easily see your investments and key numbers for your account (for ex. total value, the amount available for trading, etc.). Performance for today (equities) and one day (funds) are presented by default for your holdings.
- If you have an endowment insurance depot, you can now reinvest your money by selling current fund holdings.
- For ISK account we have added a possibility to see tax forecast. Go to your ISK account to find out more.
- You can now see account details with IBAN and BIC in Accounts and Cards.

Greetings from Swedbank’s development team

New functionality in this new version of Swedbank Private:

- Strong authentication for transfers to others accounts through security token, MBID, BankID on card
- See your total monthly savings in funds by clicking on the relevant account - ISK, Fund account and/or Endowment insurance.
- See how your funds and other securities have performed in percentage since purchase g by clicking on the relevant account - ISK, Equity trader, Fund account and/or Endowment insurance.
- View your historical fund transactions by clicking on the relevant account - ISK, Fund account
- Do you have the bank's widget with your favorites list? We have added two buttons at the bottom of the widget, The market and the Full list. The market takes you to info and news about the stock market, the Full list takes you to all your favorites.

Greetings from Swedbank’s development team
